09:12 AM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing.   Defendant Paul E Revord in court with attorney J Andrew Herbers.  Alyssa M Jay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Jay also notes that Victim B is present by Zoom video with Victim/Witness advocate.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed.  Court confirms with counsel they are prepared to proceed to plea and sentencing today.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Victim B presents statements.  Atty. Herbers had a brief conversation with his client.  Atty. Herbers advises his client wants to proceed with entering his plea today.  Court continues with the plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1& 2, Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 & 2.  Court orders Count 3 dismissed and read in.

Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Jay.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Herbers.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

70 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS (48 Days Credit IF imposed - Concurrent to Count 2 IF imposed).

Term of Probation: 1 Year

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with Victim A unless approved by the Agent.
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
-	Make best efforts to Maintain/Obtain full time employment or schooling;
-	Domestic violence counseling to be determined by Agent.  

FINE or COSTS:  $243.00;

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.


